</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A9929855BE8D7FDFFD161F275" blockId="47.[151,1436,476,791]" box="[199,1072,512,539]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="B93E3D289929855BE8D7FDFFD430F275" bold="true" box="[199,353,512,539]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe. 
<collectingCountry id="F35DA1AA9929855BE9D6FDFED778F275" box="[454,553,513,539]" name="Portugal" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: one province (Trás-os-Montes e Alto Douro).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A9929855BE8D7FDDAD656F2A1" blockId="47.[151,1436,476,791]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="B93E3D289929855BE8D7FDDAD47DF251" bold="true" box="[199,300,549,575]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Ecology.</emphasis>
The only site where 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A9AB99929855BEA32FDD9D7E9F251" authorityName="Dolichopodinae" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1767" box="[546,696,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Poecilobothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobilitatus">
<emphasis id="B93E3D289929855BEA32FDD9D7E9F251" box="[546,696,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">P. nobilitatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been encountered in 
<collectingCountry id="F35DA1AA9929855BEBCFFDDAD16FF251" box="[991,1086,549,575]" name="Portugal" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Portugal</collectingCountry>
was a permanent pasture (Lameiro) crossed by a small stream, with 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A9AB99929855BEA57FDB6D79BF20D" box="[583,714,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B93E3D289929855BEA57FDB6D7F2F20D" box="[583,675,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Populus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A9AB99929855BEAC5FDB6D662F20D" box="[725,819,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B93E3D289929855BEAC5FDB6D65CF20D" box="[725,781,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Salix</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A9AB99929855BEB77FDB6D682F20D" box="[871,979,585,611]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B93E3D289929855BEB77FDB6D6FCF20D" box="[871,941,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Rubus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
among others on its banks and a 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A9AB99929855BED2EFDB6D457F2E9" authorityName="F. M. Vázquez" authorityYear="1998" baseAuthorityName="C. Vicioso" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyrenaica">
<emphasis id="B93E3D289929855BED2EFDB6D457F2E9" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Quercus pyrenaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
dominated forest higher up the slopes. In northwestern Europe, this is a very eurytopic species that can be found in huge numbers on and near shallow water bodies in both wooded and open biotopes, where the males display conspicuous courtship behaviour (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDB9CCB9929855BEA7EFD4AD7AAF2A1" author="Lunau, K." box="[622,763,693,719]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="465 - 479" refId="ref32719" refString="Lunau, K. (1992) Mating behaviour in the long-legged fly Poecilobothrus nobilitatus L. (Diptera, Dolichopodidae): courtship behaviour, male signalling and mating success. Zoologische Beitrage, Neue Folge, 34 (3), 465 - 479." type="journal article" year="1992">Lunau 1992</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A9929855BE8D7FD27D7B6F29D" blockId="47.[151,1436,476,791]" box="[199,743,728,755]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="B93E3D289929855BE8D7FD27D400F29D" bold="true" box="[199,337,728,755]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
1.1 (very rare). Very common (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A9929855BE8D7FD03D735F379" blockId="47.[151,1436,476,791]" box="[199,612,764,791]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="B93E3D289929855BE8D7FD03D4D3F379" bold="true" box="[199,386,764,791]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Activity period.</emphasis>
August–September.
</paragraph>
